definitions.definition: The collective people of a country , state , or electoral district who are entitled to vote .
examples: The votes have been counted and the electorate has spoken.

definitions.definition: The office , or area of dominion , of an Elector ( “ a German prince entitled to elect the emperor of the Holy Roman Empire ” ) ; an electorship .
A geographical area represented by one or more elected officials ; a constituency , an electoral district .
examples: The electorate of Finchley borders on the electorate of Much-Binding-in-the-Marsh, splitting the new housing estate of Royal Cupolas.

main_definition: The collective people of a country , state , or electoral district who are entitled to vote .
secondary_definitions: ( historical ) The office , or area of dominion , of an Elector ( “ a German prince entitled to elect the emperor of the Holy Roman Empire ” ) ; an electorship .
( chiefly Australia , New Zealand ) A geographical area represented by one or more elected officials ; a constituency , an electoral district .
